data.description: ONE ACRE OF LAND WITH WOODED FLORIDA VIBES! A nearly 2,000 square foot home created with natural elements that blend peacefully with stately oak trees and native vegetation. This custom-built residence offers 3 bedrooms, 2 baths, and a 2-car garage. Thought to have been built by Lee Wetherington Homes, an award-winning local builder, known for durability and innovation. Impressively crafted double doors boldly pronounce the entrance into an incomparable house. Multiple sets of skylights, along with glass doors and windows, allow for natural lighting and bring the park-like setting indoors. The refurbished wood burn fireplace sets the stage in the main living area with silver-oak hued wood laminate flooring and vaulted ceilings. Sliding glass doors fully open to combine the interior and outdoor living spaces. It is adjacent to the originally intended formal dining room that boasts flexibility as a home office, exercise room or study with an open wall for privacy. The eat-in kitchen is in the heart of the home and has a total footprint of over three hundred square feet, including the breakfast nook, primed for a gourmet’s modern renovation. The owner’s suite is set apart from the other bedrooms and guest bath. It has another five hundred square feet of relaxation and retreat with its own fireplace and views of the treed backyard. The personal bath features a 5-piece washroom incorporating an innovatively designed soaking tub with two shower heads and waterspouts. An interior laundry room with upgraded tile flooring gives way to the finished 2-car garage with a door-opener and built-ins. Entertain outside from the screened lanai with a covered area and a swimming pool. Energy efficient solar panels have been added. Tucked away in Desoto Pines, an established community with nominal annual fees that ensure the neighborhood’s upkeep. It declares an urban renewal as recent growth nearby brings a plethora of activities and amenities to the area. Conveniently located near championship golf courses, the county maintained recreational spots like Longwood Park and Nathan Benderson Park, the mall at University Town Center, shopping, and dining options. Plus, it is a short drive to the international airport, and or I-75 for commute. And not too far from Downtown Sarasota or your choice of destination beaches.
